Great Barrier Reef Features

Source: R/data.R
gbr_feat.Rd

Coastal features within and adjacent to the Great Barrier Reef World Heritage area (such as islands, rocks and the Queensland mainland). - Major coral cay features - Major and other coral reef structures (as defined by the reef shoal edge) and tidal, drying or emergent reef areas within the Great Barrier Reef World Heritage Area.

Format

A Simple Features data.frame with 5,363 rows and 21 variables:

  • OBJECTID:

  • SORT_GBR_I:

  • LABEL_ID:

  • SUB_NO:

  • CODE:

  • UNIQUE_ID:

  • FEATURE_C:

  • GBR_NAME:

  • FEAT_NAME:

  • QLD_NAME:

  • X_LABEL:

  • GBR_ID:

  • LOC_NAME_S:

  • LOC_NAME_L:

  • X_COORD:

  • Y_COORD:

  • Area_HA:

  • GlobalID:

  • Shape_STAr:

  • Shape_STLe:

  • geometry:

Details

For full Metadata see the original GBRMPA Geoportal page info for the Great Barrier Reef Features.
